# Technical Stack & Constraints
- Framework: Next.js 14+ (App Router). Use `src/app` structure.
- Language: TypeScript (Strict mode). No `any` types.
- Styling: Tailwind CSS + Shadcn/UI.
- Backend: Firebase (Firestore, Auth, Cloud Functions).
- AI Orchestration: Firebase Genkit + Google Gemini 1.5 Pro Vision.
- Payments: Razorpay (One-time payments/Credits model).
- Icons: Lucide React.
- State Management: React Context (keep it simple).

Description: "Apply this rule when touching backend logic, Firebase, or Razorpay." globs: ["src/app/api//*", "src/lib//*"]
Technical Constraints
1. Firebase (Backend)
We use Firebase Client SDK for Auth (signInWithPopup).

We use Firebase Admin SDK in API routes (firestore().collection('audits')).

CRITICAL: Do not change the data structure in Firestore. Only read/write.

2. Razorpay (Payments)
Model: One-time Credits (Pre-paid). NO RECURRING SUBSCRIPTIONS (due to RBI mandate friction).

Flow: User buys 5 credits -> Razorpay Order Created -> Payment Success -> Webhook -> Update Firestore credits balance.

Frontend: Use useRazorpay hook. Keep the script load efficient.

3. Refactoring Safety
Logic Lock: When asked to "Refactor UI", YOU MUST NOT CHANGE functionality.

If you split a file, ensure all imports (Firebase, etc.) are preserved.